Dabiru Saleh, the judge who annulled the June 12, 1993 presidential election, won by MKO Abiola, is dead. TheCable reports that Saleh has been buried according Muslim rites in Azare, his hometown, in Bauchi on Thursday evening. Saleh, until his death, held the title of “Mutawallen” of Katagum emirate in Bauchi. He served as the Chief Judge of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) High Court. Details later… Comrade Aremu laments high rate of accidents, calls for end to cheap, callous wastage of human lives Indiscriminate Tree Felling: Bauchi punish suspects, seize, auction six truck load of charcoal Kano: Stakeholders condemn Sanusi's removal, to sue Ganduje, Assembly